{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Bug|type2=Steel}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/GO|species=Durant}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Bug|prevnum=631|prev=Heatmor|nextnum=633|next=Deino|roundleft=bl|roundright=br}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Durant\n|jname=アイアント\n|jtranslit=Aianto\n|tmname=Aiant\n|category=Iron Ant\n|typebox=1\n|type1=Bug\n|type2=Steel\n|abilityn=d\n|ability1=Swarm\n|ability2=Hustle\n|abilityd=Truant\n|ndex=632\n|udex=138\n|u2dex=194\n|karea=Mountain\n|kdex=106\n|height-ftin=1\'00"\n|height-m=0.3\n|weight-lbs=72.8\n|weight-kg=33.0\n|egggroupn=1\n|egggroup1=Bug\n|eggcycles=20\n|expyield=169\n|lv100exp=1,000,000\n|gendercode=127\n|color=Gray\n|catchrate=90\n|evtotal=2\n|evde=2\n|body=14\n|pokefordex=durant\n|generation=5\n|friendship=70\n}}\n\'\'\'Durant\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'アイアント\'\'\' \'\'Aiant\'\') is a dual-type {{2t|Bug|Steel}} {{OBP|Pokémon|species}} introduced in [[Generation V]].\n\nIt is not known to [[Evolution|evolve]] into or from any other Pokémon.\n\n==Biology==\nDurant is an insectoid Pokémon with a steel body that has three distinct sections. Its ovoid abdomen is dark gray with a light gray band wrapping around the middle and two circles resembling rivets near a jagged seam. Durant\'s thorax is slightly smaller, but identical in design with its abdomen. The only difference being one circle instead of two. Its head is spherical, containing the same light gray wrap design as its body. However, it wraps from front to back on the head. On each side of its head are large red eyes with hollow black pupils. It has two round mandibles that it uses to grab things and feed itself. The mandibles are attached below its eyes and are situated in front of its horizontally opening mouth. Atop its head are two long antennae, each tipped with small spheres. Durant has six black legs sprouting from its thorax. Each leg has one claw at its tip, except the front legs that each have two.\n\nDurant is extremely territorial. It only lives in colonies and digs mazes underground designed to be as complicated as possible. It grows steel armor to protect itself from its natural predator, {{p|Heatmor}}. When attacked, Durant gathers in groups to attack as a whole to keep Heatmor away. As seen [[BW074|in the anime]], Durant prefers to eat vegetation, namely leaves. It will attack swiftly and aggressively if bothered, but will not pursue intruders once outside of its colony.\n\n==In the anime==\n[[File:Durant anime.png|thumb|left|220px|Durant in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n===Major appearances===\nMultiple Durant debuted in \'\'[[BW074|Battling the Leaf Thieves!]]\'\', where they accidentally kidnapped [[Iris\'s Axew]] while gathering food.\n\n===Minor appearances===\nMultiple Durant appeared in \'\'[[M16|Genesect and the Legend Awakened]]\'\' as residents of [[Pokémon Hills]]. At one point, they attacked {{TRT}}.\n\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Animedexheader|Unova}}\n{{Animedexbody|BW074|Durant|Ash\'s Pokédex|Durant, the Iron Ant Pokémon. Durant build twisting tunnels in the mountains where they form their nests. They are covered with a steel armor for protection.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'Best Wishes\'\'|Unova}}\n\n==In the manga==\n[[File:Emmet Durant Adventures.png|thumb|200px|Durant in [[Pokémon Adventures]]]]\n===In the Pocket Monsters BW: The Heroes of Fire and Thunder manga===\nA Durant appeared in \'\'[[FAT3|A Very Important Thing]]\'\', under the ownership of two brothers.\n\n===In the Pokémon Adventures manga===\n{{FB|Subway Boss|Emmet}} has a Durant, which was seen next to him while {{adv|White}} was testing the [[Battle Subway]] in \'\'[[PS490|A Stormy Time in the Battle Subway]]\'\'.\n\nA Durant appeared in \'\'[[PAXY30|Pinsir Changes]]\'\'.\n\nA Durant appeared in a flashback in \'\'[[PAXY34|Charizard Transforms]]\'\'.\n\n==In the TCG==\n{{main|Durant (TCG)}}\n\n==Game data==\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Dex/Header|type=bug|type2