 {{wp|Argentine ant}}, as its jaw is similar to Durant\'s. Its coloration may be based on the natural silver coloration of the silver spiny ant (\'\'{{wp|Polyrhachis}} sp.\'\').\n\n====Name origin====\nDurant may be a combination of \'\'durable\'\' or \'\'endurance\'\' (referring to its {{t|Steel}} type) and \'\'ant\'\'.\n\nAiant may be a combination of アイアン \'\'aian\'\' (iron) and \'\'ant\'\'.\n\n==In other languages==\n{{Other languages|type=bug|type2=steel\n|ja=アイアント \'\'Aiant\'\'|jameaning=From {{tt|アイアン \'\'aian\'\'|iron}} and \'\'ant\'\'\n|fr=Fermite|frmeaning=From \'\'{{tt|fer|iron}}\'\' and \'\'Termite\'\'\n|es=Durant|esmeaning=Same as English name\n|de=Fermicula|demeaning=From \'\'{{tt|ferrum|Latin for \'iron\'}}\'\' and \'\'{{wp|Them!|Formicula}}\'\'\n|it=Durant|itmeaning=Same as English name\n|ko=아이앤트 \'\'Aiant\'\'|komeaning=Transliteration of Japanese name\n|zh_cmn=鐵蟻 / 铁蚁 \'\'Tiěyǐ\'\'|zh_cmnmeaning=Literally "Iron ant"\n|ru=Дюрант \'\'Dyurant\'\'|rumeaning=Transcription of English name\n}}\n\n<br clear="left">\n\n==Notes==\n<references />\n\n==External links==\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Bug|type2=Steel}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Bug|prevnum=631|prev=Heatmor|nextnum=633|next=Deino}}\n|}\n{{-}}\n{{Project Pokédex notice}}\n\n[[de:Fermicula]]\n[[es:Durant]]\n[[fr:Fermite]]\n[[it:Durant]]\n[[ja:アイアント]]\n[[zh:铁蚁]]'}